# Multysis v2 Coding Standards - Cursor AI Rules

## 🎯 MANDATORY STANDARDS - ALWAYS FOLLOW

### Core Tech Stack (ESTABLISHED)
- **React 19** with TypeScript - Latest React version
- **React Router v6** - Client-side routing
- **Tailwind CSS** - Utility-first CSS framework
- **Vite** - Fast build tool (Note: rolldown-vite has React 19 compatibility issues)

### React Hook Form + Zod (MANDATORY)
- **ALWAYS** use React Hook Form for all form handling
- **ALWAYS** use Zod for validation schemas
- **ALWAYS** use `@hookform/resolvers/zod` for integration
- **NEVER** use uncontrolled forms or manual validation

### React Select (MANDATORY)
- **ALWAYS** use React Select for dropdown/select components
- **NEVER** use native HTML select elements
- **ALWAYS** provide proper styling and theming

### ShadCN UI (MANDATORY)
- **ALWAYS** use ShadCN UI components for consistent design
- **NEVER** create custom components that duplicate ShadCN functionality
- **ALWAYS** use the established component variants and props
- **ALWAYS** follow ShadCN theming and styling patterns

### Authentication Patterns (ESTABLISHED)
- **Portal Login**: Phone number authentication (09XXXXXXXXX format)
- **Admin Login**: Email authentication (Note: Currently converts email to phoneNumber for API compatibility)
- **This difference is intentional and should be maintained**

### Phone Number Validation (ESTABLISHED)
- **Philippine format**: `09XXXXXXXXX` or `+639XXXXXXXXX`
- **Real-time validation** with user-friendly error messages
- **Consistent across all forms** requiring phone numbers

### Password Requirements (ESTABLISHED)
- **Minimum 8 characters**
- **At least one uppercase letter**
- **At least one lowercase letter**
- **At least one number**
- **Password confirmation matching** for signup forms

## 🏗️ Component Standards

### Component Definition Pattern (MANDATORY)
```typescript
// ✅ ALWAYS use this pattern
interface ComponentProps {
  title: string;
  onSubmit: (data: FormData) => void;
  isLoading?: boolean;
}

export const ComponentName: React.FC<ComponentProps> = ({
  title,
  onSubmit,
  isLoading = false,
}) => {
  // Component implementation
};
```

### Import Organization (MANDATORY)
```typescript
// ✅ ALWAYS follow this exact order
// 1. React imports
import React from 'react';

// 2. Third-party libraries
import { useForm } from 'react-hook-form';
import { zodResolver } from '@hookform/resolvers/zod';
import Select from 'react-select';
import { useNavigate } from 'react-router-dom';

// 3. UI Components (shadcn/ui)
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button';
import { Input } from '@/components/ui/input';
import { Label } from '@/components/ui/label';
import { Dialog, DialogContent, DialogHeader, DialogTitle } from '@/components/ui/dialog';

// 4. Custom Components
import { CustomComponent } from '@/components/custom/CustomComponent';

// 5. Hooks
import { useAuth } from '@/context/AuthContext';
import { useToast } from '@/hooks/use-toast';

// 6. Types and Schemas
import type { User } from '@/types/user';
import { userSchema, type UserInput } from '@/validations/user.schema';

// 7. Utils
import { cn } from '@/lib/utils';
```

### TypeScript Standards (MANDATORY)
```typescript
// ✅ ALWAYS use interface for object shapes
export interface User {
  id: string;
  name: string;
  email: string;
  createdAt: string;
}

// ✅ ALWAYS use type for unions and computed types
export type UserRole = 'admin' | 'user' | 'moderator';
export type UserInput = z.infer<typeof userSchema>;

// ✅ ALWAYS use Props suffix for component props
interface ComponentProps {
  data: User[];
  onSelect: (user: User) => void;
}
```

## 📝 Form Standards (MANDATORY)

### React Hook Form Pattern (ALWAYS USE)
```typescript
const formSchema = z.object({
  name: z.string().min(1, 'Name is required').min(2, 'Name must be at least 2 characters'),
  email: z.string().email('Invalid email address'),
  role: z.string().min(1, 'Role is required'),
});

export const FormComponent: React.FC<FormComponentProps> = ({ onSubmit, isLoading = false }) => {
  const {
    register,
    handleSubmit,
    setValue,
    watch,
    reset,
    formState: { errors, isSubmitting },
  } = useForm<FormData>({
    resolver: zodResolver(formSchema),
    defaultValues: {
      name: '',
      email: '',
      role: '',
    },
  });

  const handleFormSubmit = (data: FormData) => {
    onSubmit(data);
    reset();
  };

  return (
    <form onSubmit={handleSubmit(handleFormSubmit)} className="space-y-6">
      {/* Form fields */}
    </form>
  );
};
```

### React Select Pattern (ALWAYS USE)
```typescript
interface SelectOption {
  value: string;
  label: string;
  description?: string;
}

<Select
  value={options.find(option => option.value === watch('role'))}
  onChange={(selectedOption) => setValue('role', selectedOption?.value || '')}
  options={options}
  placeholder="Select a role"
  className="mt-1"
  classNamePrefix="react-select"
  isSearchable={true}
  formatOptionLabel={(option) => (
    <div className="flex flex-col">
      <span className="font-medium">{option.label}</span>
      {option.description && (
        <span className="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-1">{option.description}</span>
      )}
    </div>
  )}
  styles={{
    control: (base) => ({
      ...base,
      minHeight: '40px',
      borderColor: errors.role ? '#ef4444' : '#d1d5db',
      '&:hover': {
        borderColor: errors.role ? '#ef4444' : '#9ca3af',
      },
    }),
    option: (base, state) => ({
      ...base,
      padding: '12px',
      backgroundColor: state.isSelected ? '#3b82f6' : state.isFocused ? '#f3f4f6' : 'white',
      color: state.isSelected ? 'white' : '#374151',
    }),
    menu: (base) => ({
      ...base,
      zIndex: 9999,
    }),
  }}
/>
```

## 🎨 ShadCN UI Standards (MANDATORY)

### Component Usage (ALWAYS USE)
```typescript
// ✅ ALWAYS use ShadCN UI components with variants
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button';
import { Input } from '@/components/ui/input';
import { Label } from '@/components/ui/label';
import { Card, CardContent, CardHeader, CardTitle } from '@/components/ui/card';
import { Dialog, DialogContent, DialogHeader, DialogTitle } from '@/components/ui/dialog';
import { Badge } from '@/components/ui/badge';
import { Avatar, AvatarFallback, AvatarImage } from '@/components/ui/avatar';

// Button variants
<Button variant="default">Primary Action</Button>
<Button variant="outline">Secondary Action</Button>
<Button variant="ghost">Subtle Action</Button>
<Button variant="destructive">Delete Action</Button>
<Button size="sm">Small Button</Button>
<Button size="lg">Large Button</Button>
```

### Form Components (ALWAYS USE)
```typescript
import { Form, FormControl, FormField, FormItem, FormLabel, FormMessage } from '@/components/ui/form';

<Form {...form}>
  <form onSubmit={form.handleSubmit(onSubmit)} className="space-y-6">
    <FormField
      control={form.control}
      name="name"
      render={({ field }) => (
        <FormItem>
          <FormLabel>Name</FormLabel>
          <FormControl>
            <Input placeholder="Enter name" {...field} />
          </FormControl>
          <FormMessage />
        </FormItem>
      )}
    />
    <Button type="submit">Submit</Button>
  </form>
</Form>
```

## 🎨 Styling Standards (MANDATORY)

### ClassName Organization (ALWAYS USE)
```typescript
// ✅ ALWAYS use cn() utility for conditional classes
import { cn } from '@/lib/utils';

<div className={cn(
  'flex items-center justify-between px-4 py-2',
  'bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-md',
  'hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors',
  isActive && 'bg-primary-50 border-primary-200',
  className
)}>

// ✅ ALWAYS use consistent error styling
{errors.fieldName && (
  <p className="text-red-500 text-sm mt-1">{errors.fieldName.message}</p>
)}
```

## 🚨 Error Handling Standards (MANDATORY)

### Form Validation Errors (ALWAYS USE)
```typescript
// ✅ ALWAYS use this pattern for field errors
<div className="space-y-2">
  <Label htmlFor="name" className="text-sm font-medium text-gray-700">
    Name *
  </Label>
  <Input
    {...register('name')}
    id="name"
    placeholder="Enter name"
    className="mt-1"
  />
  {errors.name && (
    <p className="text-red-500 text-sm mt-1">{errors.name.message}</p>
  )}
</div>
```

### Toast Notifications (ALWAYS USE)
```typescript
const { toast } = useToast();

// Success
toast({
  title: 'Success',
  description: 'Operation completed successfully!',
});

// Error
toast({
  variant: 'destructive',
  title: 'Error',
  description: error.message || 'Something went wrong',
});
```

## 📁 File Structure Standards (MANDATORY)

### File Naming Conventions (ALWAYS FOLLOW)
- **Components**: PascalCase (e.g., `AddRoleModal.tsx`, `AdminLogin.tsx`)
- **Hooks**: camelCase starting with "use" (e.g., `useAuth.ts`, `useRoles.ts`)
- **Types**: PascalCase (e.g., `User.ts`, `auth.ts`)
- **Schemas**: camelCase with ".schema.ts" suffix (e.g., `auth.schema.ts`, `user.schema.ts`)
- **Pages**: PascalCase with section prefix (e.g., `AdminDashboard.tsx`, `PortalLogin.tsx`)
- **Services**: camelCase with ".service.ts" suffix (e.g., `auth.service.ts`)
- **Utils**: camelCase (e.g., `cn.ts`)

## 🎯 UI/UX Standards (ESTABLISHED)

### Responsive Design (ALWAYS FOLLOW)
- **Mobile-first approach** - Design for mobile, then enhance for desktop
- **Responsive sidebar** - Mobile drawer, desktop sidebar
- **Touch-friendly interfaces** - Appropriate button sizes and spacing
- **Adaptive layouts** - Components that work across all screen sizes

### User Experience (ALWAYS FOLLOW)
- **Loading states on buttons** - Show loading indicators during async operations
- **Form validation feedback** - Real-time validation with clear error messages
- **Error messages** - User-friendly, actionable error messages
- **Smooth transitions** - CSS transitions for better UX
- **Professional design** - Clean, modern, and consistent design language

